Title: Probable Values of the Cosmological Constant in a Holographic Theory

Authors: Petr Horava and Djordje Minic

Comments: 8 pages, harvmac (b)

Journal-ref: Phys.Rev.Lett. 85 (2000) 1610-1613

We point out that for a large class of universes, holography implies that themost probable value of the cosmological constant is zero. In four spacetimedimensions, the probability distribution takes the Baum-Hawking form,$dP\sim\exp(cM_p^2/\Lambda)d\Lambda$.